-- Hong Kong shares stay at 5-month lows, Apple suppliers sink
-- By Clement Tan
-- Tue Jan 28, 2014 03:07AM EST
-- None



HONG KONG, Jan 28 (Reuters) - Hong Kong shares stayed at five-month lows on Tuesday as turnover sagged with investors still jittery after a selloff and before key central bank meetings in the United States and Turkey.

The Hang Seng Index <.HSI> ended down 0.1 percent at 21,960.6 points, while the China Enterprises Index <.HSCE> of the leading Chinese listings in Hong Kong slipped 0.3 percent. Both closed at their lowest since August. [ID:nL3N0L21DB] Turnover dropped nearly 20 percent from Monday.